column12: Machine for folding textile sheet materials
column13: A machine for folding sheets (10) of textile-type materials includes a horizontal conveyor (12) which moves at a constant speed and which receives successive sheets (10) to be folded. The leading part of each sheet (10) leaving the discharge end of the conveyor (12) is floated by means of an air cushion (A) over a unidirectionally drivable, but normally stationary, roller (20), until a predetermined length of the sheet (10) has passed over the roller (20). The air cushion is then removed so that the sheet (10) no longer moves over the stationary roller (20) but develops a hanging fold between the conveyor (12) and the roller (20). When the apex (23) of the hanging fold corresponds to the midlength of the sheet (10), the roller (20) is rotated in the same direction and same speed as the conveyor (12) until the quarter and three-quarter points are opposite a nip defined between a pair of rollers (24, 26), whereupon the latter points are urged into the nip by another air blast (30) to form a second fold. <IMAGE>

column12: Surgical/medical irrigator with removable splash shield
column13: A surgical/medical irrigator with a handpiece in which there is a pump from which irrigating fluid is discharged. The irrigating fluid is discharged from a discharge tube attached to the handpiece. Irrigating fluid is removed from the site to which it is applied through a suction tube also attached to the handpiece. A splash shield is removably attached to the ends of the discharge and suction tubes to limit fluid discharge. The splash shield is formed with a discharge chamber into which the fluid from the discharge chamber is discharged. The splash shield has a bore that leads from the discharge chamber to the suction tube through which fluid is drawn away from the discharge chamber. Seals between the discharge and suction tubes and the splash shield prevent fluid flow between the tubes and the splash shield.

column12: Solenoid operated latching strike
column13: A latching strike assembly for a door lock has a body ( 1, 201, 301 ) adapted to be fitted to a doorjamb. A latching strike ( 4, 204, 304 ) is mounted to the body ( 1, 201, 301 ) and defines a boundary of the latch bolt recess ( 3, 203, 303 ) of the body ( 1, 201, 301 ). The latching strike ( 1, 204, 304 ) is pivotable between open and closed positions for releasing and retaining a latch bolt ( 100 ) respectively. A bi-stable detent ( 7, 207, 307 ) is displaceable between a sable locking position at which the detent ( 7, 207, 307 ) engages the latching strike ( 4, 204, 304 ) to lock the latching strike ( 4, 204, 304 ) in the closed position and a stable unlocking position at which the detent ( 7, 207, 307 ) is disengaged from the latching strike ( 4, 204, 304 ), thereby enabling the latching strike ( 4, 204, 304 ) to be deflected to the open position by the latch bolt ( 100 ). The detent ( 7, 207, 307 ) may be displaced between the locking and unlocking positions either by a single solenoid ( 314 ) or by two separate solenoids ( 14, 15, 214, 215 ).

column12: AUTOMATIC CONTROL INITIATION FOR A HARVESTER
column13: A harvester with a control system responsive to at least one crop processi ng variable for automatically controlling forward speed of the harvester includ es a crop presence responsive switch connected to an automatic harvester control syste m. The switch, preferably a proximity switch responsive to movement of the feed er house drum from an empty feeder house limit position, provides a signal in response to crop entering the feeder house for initiating the automatic speed control of the harvester after the header receives the crop and prior to the crop entering the processing structure. The automatic control initiation structure is particularly useful with an automatic combine throughput control and eliminates unstable operati on resulting from delayed control initiation. The switch is part of an adjustab le down stop mechanism for the feeder house drum.

column12: Automatic control initiation for a harvester
column13: A harvester with a control system responsive to at least one crop processing variable for automatically controlling forward speed of the harvester includes a crop presence responsive switch connected to an automatic harvester control system. The switch, preferably a proximity switch responsive to movement of the feeder house drum from an empty feeder house limit position, provides a signal in response to crop entering the feeder house for initiating the automatic speed control of the harvester after the header receives the crop and prior to the crop entering the processing structure. The automatic control initiation structure is particularly useful with an automatic combine throughput control and eliminates unstable operation resulting from delayed control initiation. The switch is part of an adjustable down stop mechanism for the feeder house drum.

column12: UNA COSECHADORA CON INSTALACION PARA INICIAR UNA FUNCION DE CONTROL AUTOMATICO Y EL METODO DE INICACION DE CONTROL QUE LLEVA A LA PRACTICA
column13: Estructura y método para iniciar el control automático de una cosechadora combinada. Una cosechadora con un sistema de control que responde a al menos una variable de procesamiento de cultivo para controlar automáticamente la velocidad en marcha delante de la cosechadora incluye un interruptor que responde a la presencia de cultivo conectado a un sistema de control automático para la cosechadora: El interruptor, preferiblemente un interruptor de proximidad que responde al movimiento del tambor del alimentador desde una posición límite de alojamiento alimentador vacío, provee una senal en respuesta al cultivo que ingresa al alimentador para iniciar el control de velocidad automático de la cosechadora después que el cabezal recibe el cultivo y antes que el cultivo ingrese a la estructura de procesamiento. La estructura de iniciación de control automático es particularmente útil con un control automático de rendimiento de una cosechadora combinada y elimina la operación inestable que resulta de una iniciación retrasada del control. El interruptor es parte de un mecanismo de tope descendente ajustable para el tambor del alojamiento alimentador.
column15: BURKE DANIEL JAMES;;COERS BRUCE ALAN

column12: Colheitadeira, e, método de iniciar controle automático de uma combinada
column13: "COLHEITADEIRA, E, MéTODO DE INICIAR CONTROLE AUTOMáTICO DE UMA COMBINADA". Uma colheitadeira com um sistema de controle responsivo a pelo menos uma variável de processamento de produto de safra para controlar automaticamente a velocidade à frente da colheitadeira inclui um comutador responsivo à presença de produto de safra conectado a um sistema de controle automático de colheitadeira. O comutador, de preferência, um comutador de proximidade responsivo à movimentação do tambor de alojamento do alimentador de uma posição limite de alojamento do alimentador vazio, provê um sinal em resposta ao produto de safra entrando no alojamento do alimentador para iniciar o controle automático de velocidade da colheitadeira após a espigadeira receber o produto de safra e antes do mesmo entrar na estrutura de processamento. A estrutura de início de controle automático é particularmente útil com um controle automático de produção de colheitadeira e elimina a operação instável resultante de início retardado de controle. O comutador faz parte de um mecanismo ajustável de batente descendente para o tambor do alojamento do alimentador.

column12: Grand piano composite piano action
column13: Composite or plastic molded articles used in a grand piano action. A piano action actuates in response to depression on a piano key to swing a hammer into a piano string. The articles are assembled to form a piano action with significantly less dynamic mass which is much more responsive to the touch. In addition, the new action provides the valuable collateral benefits of increased efficiency of manufacture and maintenance. The invention also provides the capability to achieve true half stroke design in both the sharp and white keys. Additionally, the application discloses a universal composite grand piano action that is capable of being installed into any brand of grand piano.

column12: UNIVERSAL GRAND PIANO PIANO ACTION WITH SIMULTANEOUS HALF STROKE KEYBOARD DESIGN CAPABILITY
column13: A universal grand piano piano action that has adjustable connections between the repetition base, heel, and rest cushion bracket of the piano action to provide a one-size-fits-all after-market replacement piano action for any grand piano. Other components of the grand piano piano action, such as the jack and flanges, may require specific design and manufacture for each brand of grand piano. This invention is the first piano action to allow for true simultaneous half stroke keyboard design for both the white and sharp keys of a piano and includes the method for installing such.

column12: HAMMER ASSEMBLY FOR GRAND PIANO
column13: A hammer assembly for a grand piano comprising: a hammer, a hammer shank, a tubular lever interface, and a moveable knuckle. A grand piano tubular lever interface comprises: a deep socket; a set of two hinge pin attachment holes; a void area; and a moveable knuckle visual location system. A moveable knuckle comprises: a spline; a resilient core; a synthetic buckskin wear surface, and a moveable knuckle visual location system. Novel hammer assembly allows for a direct lever relationship between hammer shank and knuckle without requirement of a forked end hammer shank with knuckle slot. Best mode spline comprises: an upright rectangular portion and a wide base portion, wherein wide base portion includes an intricate shape. Intricate shape comprises: at least one recess area and at least one protrusion area. The inverse of intricate shape is included on the bottom of the tubular lever interface. Moveable knuckle visual location system further comprises at least one pointer located on the moveable knuckle which fits snuggly into one of several notches on the tubular lever interface. Moveable knuckle can be visually located onto tubular lever interface at any one of multiple distinct locations along a range that runs parallel to the length of the hammer shank and the length of tubular lever interface. The moveable knuckle visual location system allows for custom configuration of a specifically dimensioned hammer assembly with custom “tubular lever interface center-to center” dimension to refurbish any brand of grand piano from one stock-set of hammer assembly components.

column13: Composite or plastic molded articles used in a grand piano piano action. A piano action actuates in response to depression on a piano key to swing a hammer into a piano string. The articles comprise a grand piano piano action with significantly less dynamic mass which is much more responsive to the touch. In addition, the new action provides the valuable collateral benefits of increased efficiency of manufacture and maintenance. The invention also provides the capability to achieve true simultaneous half stroke design in both the sharp and white keys. Additionally, the application discloses a universal composite grand piano piano action that is capable of convenient installation into any brand of grand piano.

column12: HAMMER ASSEMBLY FOR GRAND PIANO
column13: A hammer assembly for a grand piano comprises a hammer, a hammer shank, a tubular lever interface, a moveable knuckle, and a moveable knuckle visual location system The novel hammer assembly allows for a direct lever relationship between hammer shank and knuckle without requirement of a forked end hammer shank with knuckle slot The moveable knuckle can be visually located onto tubular lever interface at anyone of multiple distinct locations along a range that runs parallel to the length of the hammer shank and the length of tubular lever interface The moveable knuckle visual location system allows for custom configuration of a specifically dimensioned hammer assembly with custom "tubular lever interface center-to center" dimension to refurbish any brand of grand piano from one stock-set of hammer assembly components.

column12: HAMMER SHANK AND SHANK BUTT FOR PIANO
column13: A hammer shank and shank butt for a grand piano with greatly improved rigidity and the collateral benefits of increased efficiency of manufacture and maintenance. Hammer shank comprises a long cylindrical member that is connected at one end to a traditional grand piano hammer and at the other end to a novel shank butt. Shank butt comprises: a hammer shank hole, a knuckle slot, a set of two flange attachment holes, and a void area. A traditional grand piano knuckle is attached to the knuckle slot. The shank butt is connected to the repetition flange of the piano. Thus, hammer shank is not directly connected to these members and thus can remain an integral cylindrical member without holes, notches, or voids, thereby allowing for a lighter, more rigid sub-member yielding hammer assembly with less mass. The invention provides the capability for a piano to be played with less touch weight on the keys and therefore provides a more responsive piano keyboard. The invention also allows for full “retrofitability” of hammer assembly into all existing grand piano brands. Embodiments include a composite shank butt that is a molded article and a composite hammer shank that is an extruded or molded article.
column15: CLARK BRUCE E;;BURKE KEVIN;;BURGETT KIRK

column12: Hammer assembly for grand piano
column13: A hammer assembly for a grand piano comprising: a hammer, a hammer shank, a tubular lever interface, and a moveable knuckle. A grand piano tubular lever interface comprises: a deep socket; a set of two hinge pin attachment holes; a void area; and a moveable knuckle visual location system. A moveable knuckle comprises: a spline; a resilient core; a synthetic buckskin wear surface, and a moveable knuckle visual location system. Novel hammer assembly allows for a direct lever relationship between hammer shank and knuckle without requirement of a forked end hammer shank with knuckle slot. Best mode spline comprises: an upright rectangular portion and a wide base portion, wherein wide base portion includes an intricate shape. Intricate shape comprises: at least one recess area and at least one protrusion area. The inverse of intricate shape is included on the bottom of the tubular lever interface. Moveable knuckle visual location system further comprises at least one pointer located on the moveable knuckle which fits snuggly into one of several notches on the tubular lever interface. Moveable knuckle can be visually located onto tubular lever interface at any one of multiple distinct locations along a range that runs parallel to the length of the hammer shank and the length of tubular lever interface. The moveable knuckle visual location system allows for custom configuration of a specifically dimensioned hammer assembly with custom “tubular lever interface center-to center” dimension to refurbish any brand of grand piano from one stock-set of hammer assembly components.
column15: CLARK BRUCE E;;BURKE KEVIN;;BURGETT KIRK

column12: Method and apparatus for multiple access over randomized slots with collision detection in a cable telephony system
column13: A method and apparatus in a communications system (100) for providing communications units (134) access to the communications system (100). The communications. system (100) includes a cable distribution network (106) with an base communications unit (102) and a number of downstream communications units (134) all connected to the cable distribution network (106). A plurality of channels are used to transmit data between the base communications unit (102) and the downstream communications units (134). A first set of channels are used primarily for access the communications system (100) and a second set of channels are used for transmitting data within the communications system (100) after access to the communications system (100) has been gained. The base communications unit (102) sends a first type of data transmission including an identification of access channels used for requesting access to the communications system (100). The base communications unit (102) assigns channels within the second set of channels response to receiving a request for access to the communications system (100) on the first set of channels. A mechanism also is provided for handling collisions in transmissions between the downstream communications units (134) to the base communications unit (102) in attempting to gain access to the communications system (100).

column12: Surgical/medical irrigator with rechargeable battery pack
column13: An irrigator (  20  ) useful for surgical and medical procedures. The irrigator includes a handpiece (  22  ) to which a tip assembly (  30  ) is attached. column12: PARTIALLY PRIVATE AND VERIFIABLE DATA EXCHANGE
column13: A transactional medical data exchange provides a combination of public and private communication channels through which parties to a transaction, such as a medical care provider and a health insurance provider, may exchange information. When such an exchange is needed, the parties create records on the public communication channel that serve as a publicly viewable record that communication has begun. Information from these public records are used to share messages, along with messages, files, and other information related to care, via a private communication channel. Each private communication is sent and stored with unique authenticating data to form a chain of verifiable transactions. When communication is done, each party creates records on the public communication that request and acknowledge that communication is now complete and provide publicly viewable information that can be used to verify and authenticate each private message by itself, or in combination with others.

column12: IMPULSE CLOCK SYSTEM
column13: A clock system of the impulse type consisting of stepper motor driven secondary clocks (16) and a master control (10). Each secondary clock (16) includes a stepper motor (22) directly driving the minute hand (26), an hour hand (28) driven by the minute hand (26), and an emitter (90) and detector (92) on opposite sides of a gear (50) of the movement and coacting with a window (50a) in the gear to determine the absolute position of the clock for comparison to the master control time. At five minutes before 6:00, the sensor, (64) of each secondary clock (16) is activated by a signal from the master control (10) and a series of reset pulses are thereafter transmitted to the secondary clocks (16) with each secondary clock stopping as the window (50a) in its drive train gear (50) moves into alignment with the emitter (90) and detector (92) of its sensor mechanism (64), whereafter all of the remaining clocks are moved to 6:00 by a rapid pulse train.

column12: Agricultural work machine having an unloading system for unloading an agricultural product
column13: An agricultural work machine for performing harvesting operations. The agricultural work machine includes a support structure. An unloading system is coupled to the support structure and is configured to transport an agricultural product received from a hopper to an off-machine location. A positioning system is configured to adjust at least one of an elevation, a length and a rotational position of the transfer assembly to position the discharge chute. column12: DESIGN AND METHOD FOR INSTALLATION OF STEERING AXLE IN TRANSPORT POSITION AND AGRICULTURAL MACHINE COMPRISING SAID STEERING AXLE
column13: The inventions relate to reduction in the dimensions of agricultural machines during transportation. A unit of a steering axle has transverse telescoping axles and hub assemblies on the telescoping axles. These are attached to front and rear hydraulic cylinders to move the wheel hub assemblies both in axial direction and for turning them. An agricultural machine is equipped with said steering axle. In operation of the machine said hydraulic cylinders are used to control the hubs for wheels turning. For reduction of the width of steering axle during transportation of the agricultural machine the telescoping connection is retracted followed by reduction of the distance between the hubs. It also is possible to turn them thus reducing the overall dimensions in the area of axles of steering wheels.

column12: Impulse clock system
column13: A master secondary clock system of the analog impulse type consisting of separate motor driven secondary clocks and a master control unit. The secondary clocks can be set at any time by an appropriate signal from the master clock so that even widely scattered secondary clocks can be brought at any time to the correct time. In one disclosed embodiment, the secondary clocks are moved by a series of rapid pulses form the master clock to a predetermined known time, the secondary clocks are brought into registry, the master clock calculates the time disparity between the registration time and the real time, and the secondary clocks are moved in unison to the real time. In another disclosed embodiment in which each secondary clock includes a microprocessor, an encoded digital signal representing the real time is transmitted to the secondary clocks, the secondary clocks move to a predetermined known time, a microprocessor in each secondary clock calculates the time disparity between the known time and the real time upon arrival of the second clock at the known time, and the secondary clocks thereafter move to the real time.

column12: Impulse clock system
column13: A master/secondary clock system of the impulse type consisting of stepper motor driven secondary clocks and a master control unit. At five minutes before a predetermined registration time, for example 6:00, the sensor of each secondary clock movement is activated by a reverse polarity signal from the master control unit and a series of reset pulses are thereafter transmitted to the secondary clocks with each secondary clock stopping as the window in its drive train gear moves into alignment with the emitter and detector of its sensor mechanism. After this five minute pulse reset phase to correct clocks that are five or less minutes fast, the master control unit transmits a rapid pulse train so as to quickly move all of the remaining clocks to the 6:00 position with each clock being halted at the 6:00 position by movement of the window of its gear into alignment with the emitter and detector of the sensor mechanism of that clock. Following the rapid pulse phase to bring all of the clocks into the correct time mode, normal one minute pulsing of the clocks is resumed by the master control unit.
column15: BURKE MICHAEL P;;BOGDAN STEPHEN A;;EMAUS BRUCE D

column12: máquina de trabalho agrìcola, sistema de transporte acoplável a uma máquina de trabalho agrìcola com uma direção operacional, e, método para reduzir o desgaste de pneu em uma máquina de trabalho agrìcola

column12: Transducer positioning apparatus
column13: Apparatus for moving a transducer carriage intermittently along a tract relative to a recording medium employs belting arranged in a closed loop that is tensioned by engagement around at least one idler and connected to the carriage. Belt end segments comprising the loop are wrapped in opposite directions around the periphery of a stepping motor-driven capstan and their ends are secured thereto at axially spaced apart locations thereon. The belting and idlers are arranged so that all of the belt segments wrapped around the capstan remain parallel to the carriage track as the capstan rotates so as to advance the carriage a maximum number of increments along its track.

column12: DISPOSITIF DE POSITIONNEMENT POUR TRANSDUCTEURS
column13:
a. Dispositif de positionnement pour transducteurs.

b. Dispositif pour entraîner un chariot portant un transducteur de façon intermittente le long d'une trajectoire par rapport à un support d'enregistrement utilisant une courroie formant une boucle sans fin qui est tendue en passant autour d'au moins une poulie libre et qui est reliée au chariot. Les extrémités de la courroie s'enroulent suivant des directions opposées autour d'un cabestan entraîné par un moteur pas à pas et leurs extrémités sont fixées à celui-ci à des emplacements espacés le long de son axe. La courroie et les poulies sont arrangées pour que les segments enroulés autour du cabestan restent parallèles à la trajectoire du chariot afin de faire avancer ce dernier d'un nombre maximal d'incréments le long de sa trajectoire.

c. S'applique aux appareils d'enregistrement et concerne plus particulièrement l'entraînement du transducteur de lecture et d'enregistrement de ces appareils.

column12: Method and apparatus for setting or modifying programmable parameter in power driven wheelchair
column13: A method and apparatus for setting or modifying a programmable operating parameter associated with a power driven wheelchair is provided. In one embodiment, the method includes: a) operating a user interface device associated with a power driven wheelchair in a programming mode, b) selecting a programmable operating parameter associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device, c) selecting a value for the programmable operating parameter using the user interface device, and d) saving the selected value for the programmable operating parameter in a portion of a storage device associated with the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device. A method and apparatus for selecting one or more programmable parameter sets from a portable storage medium and saving the selected sets to a local storage device associated with a power driven wheelchair and vice versa is also provided.

column12: Wheelchair with a programmable operating parameter that can be selected in a programming mode
column13: A power driven wheelchair capable of setting or modifying a programmable parameter and a method associated with a power driven wheelchair for setting or modifying a programmable parameter are disclosed. The power driven wheelchair includes a user interface device adapted to operate in a programming mode; and a first storage device in operative communication with the user interface device with at least a portion designated for storage of a programmable operating parameter associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair. The user interface device is used to select the programmable operating parameter, select a value for the programmable operating parameter, and save the selected value for the programmable operating parameter in the portion of the first storage device, such that when the power driven wheelchair exits the programming mode, the programmable operating parameter is set to the selected value for operation of the wheelchair. Further disclosed is an apparatus associated with a power driven wheelchair for communicating a programmable parameter set including a user interface device associated with a power driven wheelchair and adapted to operate in a programming mode; a portable storage medium in operative communication with the user interface device with at least a portion designated for storage of one or more programmable parameter sets associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair; and a local storage device in operative communication with the user interface device with at least a portion designated for storage of one or more programmable parameter sets associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair. The user interface device is used to select one or more programmable parameter sets from the portable storage medium and save the selected programmable parameter sets to the local storage device or vice versa.

column12: Geranyl diphosphate synthase from mint
column13: A cDNA encoding geranyl diphosphate synthase from peppermint has been isolated and sequenced, and the corresponding amino acid sequence has been determined. Accordingly, an isolated DNA sequence (SEQ ID No:1) is provided which codes for the expression of geranyl diphosphate synthase (SEQ ID No:2) from peppermint (Mentha piperita). In other aspects, replicable recombinant cloning vehicles are provided which code for geranyl diphosphate synthase or for a base sequence sufficiently complementary to at least a portion of the geranyl diphosphate synthase DNA or RNA to enable hybridization therewith (e.g., antisense geranyl diphosphate synthase RNA or fragments of complementary geranyl diphosphate synthase DNA which are useful as polymerase chain reaction primers or as probes for geranyl diphosphate synthase or related genes). In yet other aspects, modified host cells are provided that have been transformed, transfected, infected and/or injected with a recombinant cloning vehicle and/or DNA sequence encoding geranyl diphosphate synthase. Thus, systems and methods are provided for the recombinant expression of geranyl diphosphate synthase that may be used to facilitate the production, isolation and purification of significant quantities of recombinant geranyl diphosphate synthase for subsequent use, to obtain expression or enhanced expression of geranyl diphosphate synthase in plants in order to enhance the production of monoterpenoids, to produce geranyl diphosphate in cancerous cells as a precursor to monoterpenoids having anti-cancer properties or may be otherwise employed for the regulation or expression of geranyl diphosphate synthase or the production of geranyl diphosphate.

column12: Method and apparatus for setting or modifying programmable parameter in power driven wheelchair
column13: A method and apparatus for setting or modifying a programmable operating parameter associated with a power driven wheelchair is provided. In one embodiment, the method includes: a) operating a user interface device associated with a power driven wheelchair in a programming mode, b) selecting a programmable operating parameter associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device, c) selecting a value for the programmable operating parameter using the user interface device, and d) saving the selected value for the programmable operating parameter in a portion of a storage device associated with the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device. A method and apparatus for selecting one or more programmable parameter sets from a portable storage medium and saving the selected sets to a local storage device associated with a power driven wheelchair and vice versa is also provided.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SETTING OR MODIFYING PROGRAMABLE PARAMETER IN POWER DRIVEN WHEELCHAIR
column13: A method and apparatus for setting or modifying a programmable operating parameter associated with a power driven wheelchair is provided. In one embodiment, the method includes: a) operating a user interface device associated with a power driven wheelchair in a programming mode, b) selecting a programmable operating parameter associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device, c) selecting a value for the programmable operating parameter using the user interface device, and d) saving the selected value for the programmable operating parameter in a portion of a storage device associated with the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device. A method and apparatus for selecting one or more programmable parameter sets from a portable storage medium and saving the selected sets to a local storage device associated with a power driven wheelchair and vice versa is also provided.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SETTING OR MODIFYING PROGRAMABLE PARAMETER IN POWER DRIVEN WHEELCHAIR
column15: PETERS DARRYL;;JAENKE BRUCE A;;BURKE CARRIE L;;CHOPCINSKI GARY E

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SETTING OR MODIFYING PROGRAMMABLE PARAMETER IN POWER DRIVEN WHEELCHAIR
column13: A method and apparatus for setting or modifying a programmable operating parameter associated with a power driven wheelchair is provided. In one embodiment, the method includes: a) operating a user interface device associated with a power driven wheelchair in a programming mode, b) selecting a programmable operating parameter associated with operation of the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device, c) selecting a value for the programmable operating parameter using the user interface device, and d) saving the selected value for the programmable operating parameter in a portion of a storage device associated with the power driven wheelchair using the user interface device. A method and apparatus for selecting one or more programmable parameter sets from a portable storage medium and saving the selected sets to a local storage device associated with a power driven wheelchair and vice versa is also provided.
column15: PETERS DARRYL;;JAENKE BRUCE A;;BURKE CARRIE L;;CHOPCINSKI GARY E

column12: elemento de eixo extensível para uma colheitadeira agrícola
column13: elemento de eixo extensível para uma colheitadeira agrícola é provido um elemento de eixo extensível (146 ou 148) para um eixo pivô de uma colheitadeira agrícola (100), o elemento de eixo extensível (146 ou 148) tendo uma porção telescópica alongada (400) com superfícies de mancal para ser recebidas de forma deslizante em um elemento de eixo externo (142 ou 144), em que a porção telescópica alongada (400) é formada integral com a armação c, e apóia-se nela, para suportar uma junta de direção (158 ou 160).
column15: BRUCE ALAN COERS;;DANIEL JAMES BURKE;;ERIC ALLAN RISIUS;;RYAN PATRICK MACKIN

column12: Extendible Axle Member For The Rear Of An Agricultural Harvester
column13: An extendible axle member ( 146 or 148 ) is provided for a pivoting axle of an agricultural harvester ( 100 ), the extendible axle member ( 146 or 148 ) having an elongate telescopic portion ( 400 ) with bearing surfaces for being slidably received in an outer axle member ( 142 or 144 ), wherein the elongate telescopic portion ( 400 ) is formed integral with and abuts a C-frame for supporting a steering knuckle ( 158 or 160 ).
column14: MACKIN RYAN PATRICK;;BURKE DANIEL JAMES;;COERS BRUCE ALAN;;RISIUS ERIC ALLEN
column15: MACKIN RYAN PATRICK;;BURKE DANIEL JAMES;;COERS BRUCE ALAN;;RISIUS ERIC ALLEN

column12: Unloading system for an agricultural harvester
column13: An unloading system for an agricultural harvester includes a grain tank (16); a door (56) at the outlet of the grain tank (16) that is disposed to control the flow of grain out of the grain tank (16); a door actuator (84) coupled to the door (56) that is disposed to open and close the door; a first conveyor (30) disposed to receive grain passing through the door (56); a first conveyor drive motor (80) coupled to the first conveyor (30) to drive the first conveyor (30); and a control circuit (72) coupled to both the door actuator (84) and the first conveyor drive motor (80). The control circuit (72) being configured to close the door (56) prior to shutting off the first conveyor (30) in response to a command to shut down the unloading system.
column15: MACKIN RYAN PATRICK;;BURKE DANIEL J;;COERS BRUCE A;;DEPOORTER MARK CHARLES

column12: Method for concentrating light and light concentrator
column13: A system for a gas turbine engine includes an igniter event conductor. The igniter event conductor has a first portion adjacent an igniter of the engine and in a combustion chamber of the engine and a second portion apart from the igniter and apart from the combustion chamber. The conductor is adapted to conduct an aspect of an igniter event at the igniter from the first portion to the second portion. A sensor is coupled to the second portion of the conductor to sense the aspect of the igniter event.
column15: BURKE DANIEL S;;STEWART JEFFREY TAYLOR;;CAUSEY JIM;;HACKENBERG MICHAEL;;HARRAR BRUCE

column12: Fuel economy monitoring system for engines of vehicles
column13: A fuel economy monitoring system for vehicle engines including a linear diaphragm vacuum motor connected to the intake manifold. Movement of the diaphragm is indicated by means of a multicolored filter and lamp arrangement which transmits colors through a fiber optic bundle, which colors are quickly observable by a driver within his peripheral vision to indicate by the observed engine intake manifold vacuum how the driver's throttle settings are affecting the fuel economy of the engine.
column15: DIXSON BRUCE E;;GAYTON JOHN E;;LOWERY DENNIS J;;BURKE WILLIAM F

column12: DOPA-functionalized, branched, poly(aklylene oxide) adhesives
column13: The invention describes DOPA functionalized, branched, polyalkylene oxide materials that are useful as adhesives.

column12: Unloading system for an agricultural harvester
column13: An unloading system for an agricultural harvester includes a grain tank (16); a door (56) at the outlet of the grain tank (16) that is disposed to control the flow of grain out of the grain tank (16); a door actuator (84) coupled to the door (56) that is disposed to open and close the door; a first conveyor (30) disposed to receive grain passing through the door (56); a first conveyor drive motor (80) coupled to the first conveyor (30) to drive the first conveyor (30); and a control circuit (72) coupled to both the door actuator (84) and the first conveyor drive motor (80). The control circuit (72) being configured to close the door (56) prior to shutting off the first conveyor (30) in response to a command to shut down the unloading system.
column15: MACKIN RYAN PATRICK;;BURKE DANIEL J;;COERS BRUCE A;;DEPOORTER MARK CHARLES

column12: Unload rate control for an unloading system in an agricultural harvester
column13: An agricultural harvester includes a support frame and a hopper coupled to the support frame. The hopper is configured to store an agricultural product during a harvesting operation. An unloading system is coupled to the support frame. The unloading system is configured to transport agricultural product received from the hopper to an off-machine location. The unloading system includes a metering gate, a transfer conveyance, at least one sensor, and an electrical processing circuit. The metering gate is positioned near a bottom of the hopper and in communication with an interior of the hopper. The transfer conveyance has an inlet end and a discharge end. The inlet end is in communication with the metering gate. The at least one sensor provides an output signal representing an operating parameter associated with an unload rate of agricultural product through the transfer conveyance during an unloading operation. The electrical processing circuit is coupled to the metering gate and the at least one sensor. The electrical processing circuit controls a position of the metering gate, dependent upon the output signal.
column15: MACKIN RYAN PATRICK;;BURKE DANIEL JAMES;;COERS BRUCE ALAN;;DEPOORTER MARK CHARLES

column12: IMPLANTABLE BIOCOMPATIBLE EXPANDER SUITABLE FOR TREATMENT OF CONSTRICTIONS OF BODY LUMEN
column13: An implantable biocompatible expander suitable for implantation into a urinary duct, comprises an elongated sinusoidal ring comprising at least two proximal prongs and at least two distal prongs, wherein the expander is resiliently deformable from a relaxed radially expanded orientation to a radially contracted orientation suitable for transluminal delivery through the urinary duct. The expander is configured to exert an outward radial force against a wall of the urinary duct when in-situ within the urinary duct. In particular, the expander is suitable for treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia and configured for implantation into the prostatic urethra between, and substantially spanning the prostatic urethra between, the bladder neck and external sphincter.

column12: conjunto de tubo de descarregamento, e, máquina de trabalho combinada
column13: CONJUNTO DE TUBO DE DESCARREGAMENTO, E, MáQUINA DE TRABALHO COMBINADA. é descrita uma combinada agrícola que tem um tubo de descarregamento flexivel para descarregar os conteúdos de um tanque graneleiro posicionado na combinada. O tubo de descarregamento inclui primeiro e segundo tubos conectados por um par de juntas articuladas em um tubo intermediário. As juntas articuladas são atuadas independentemente uma da outra tanto por energia elétrica quanto energia hidráulica para prover uma faixa de movimento significativamente maior que a encontrada em combinadas atuais. Uma série de trados, conectada por meio de juntas flexíveis, move material em grão através de um tubo de descarregamento. As juntas articuladas duplas permitem que o descarregador seja convenientemente localizado na combinada com uma mínima interferência no volume total da unidade.

column12: FLEXIBLE UNLOADING TUBE
column13: An agricultural combine has a flexible unloading tube for discharging the contents of a grain tank positioned on the combine. The unloading tube includes first and second tubes connected by a pair of swivel joints on an intermediate tube. The swivel joints are actuated independent of one another by either electrical or hydraulic power to provide a range of motion significantly greater than found in current combines. A series of augers, connected through flexible joints, move grain material through the unloading tube. The double swivel joints enable the unloader to be conveniently located in the combine with a minimum intrusion on the overall volume of the unit.

column12: NONLINEAR EQUALIZER TO CORRECT FOR MEMORY EFFECTS OF A TRANSMITTER
column13: Techniques for correcting for memory effects of a transmitter are described. In an exemplary design, a receiver obtains input samples including a desired signal transmitted by a transmitter having memory effects. The receiver performs nonlinear equalization on the input samples to obtain first equalized samples, performs linear equalization on the input samples to obtain second equalized samples, and determines output samples based on the first and second equalized samples. The nonlinear equalization corrects for the memory effects and nonlinearities of the transmitter and possibly nonlinearities and memory effects of the receiver. The receiver may jointly determine coefficients for both linear and nonlinear equalization based on an adaptive algorithm. The receiver processes (e.g., demodulates and decodes) the output samples to recover data sent in the desired signal by the transmitter.

column12: Elevator conveyor with force sensor for detecting the throughput of a combine

column12: AGRICULTURAL HARVESTER WITH PROPULSION LOAD SHIFTING BETWEEN DUAL ENGINES
column13: An agricultural harvester includes a first power unit which is couplable with a first primary load. The first primary load includes a threshing system load. A second power unit has a threshold power output and is couplable with a second primary load. The second primary load includes a propulsion load. A first motor/generator is mechanically coupled with the first power unit. A second motor/generator is mechanically coupled with the second power unit. The second motor/generator and the first motor/generator are electrically coupled together. At least one electrical processing circuit is coupled with each of the first motor/generator and the second motor/generator. The at least one electrical processing circuit is configured for selectively transferring electrical power from the first motor/generator to the second motor/generator, when the second power unit is at or above the threshold power output.

column13: The invention relates to Package (1) comprising: a flexible pouch (3) containing a stack of tissues (5), the pouch comprising a top surface (7), a bottom surface (9), a side surface (11, 12, 14), a pre-formed first dispensing aperture (13) in the top surface and a cover member (15) covering the first dispensing aperture, and a relatively rigid re-usable dispensing device (17) comprising attachment means (18, 33, 35, 37, 40, 41, 43, 45, 47, 55, 56, 59, 60)for releasable attachment to the pouch, characterised in that the cover member (15) is completely removable from the first dispensing aperture (13), the top surface (7) of the pouch comprising a sealing area (21) , which sealing area forms a substantially closed contour around the first dispensing aperture (13), the dispensing device (17) comprising a base member (23, 39, 47, 56, 58) having a second dispensing aperture (25, 46, 49, 50), a connecting area (27, 47, 56, 58) for sealingly engaging the sealing area (21) of the pouch, and a closure member (29, 32, 36, 38, 51, 55, 60) for sealingly closing the second dispensing aperture (25, 46, 49, 50) by contacting the base member (23, 47, 56, 58). column13: CONJUNTO DE FACAS DE AÇçO ALTERNADA DE UM IMPLEMENTO AGRíCOLA, E, CONJUNTO DE ACIONAMENTO DA FACA DE AÇçO ALTERNADA DE UM IMPLEMENTO AGRÍCOLA. É descrito um conjunto de facas de ação alternada de um implemento agrícola que inclui primeira e segunda facas de ação alternada alongadas dispostas ao longo de uma borda dianteira de um implemento agrícola, as facas de ação alternada sendo dispostas extremidade a extremidade e estendendo-se colinearmente para alternância simultânea em direções opostas, a primeira e segunda facas de ação alternada sendosuportadas para movimento deslizante no implemento agrícola em uma direção lateral no geral perpendicular à direção de deslocamento do implemento agrícola à medida que ele desloca através de um campo agrícola colhendo lavoura, uma primeira alavanca em cotovelo acoplada na primeira faca de ação alternada para alternar a dita faca, uma segunda alavanca em cotovelo acoplada na segunda faca de ação alternada para alternar a segunda faca de ação alternada, e um acionamento comum acoplado na primeira e segunda alavancas em cotovelo para acionar tanto a primeira quanto a segunda alavancas em cotovelo em direções opostas, simultaneamente.

column12: BELTED GRAIN TANK FLOOR
column13: A grain tank on a crop harvester includes a belted conveyor floor for moving grain in the grain tank toward an opening through which the grain tank is emptied. A sensor determines when the grain has depleted the tank to a substantially low level and activates the floor to remove the remainder of the grain material. A flexible strip between the active floor and the sidewalls of the grain container ensure that grain loss is minimized, if not eliminated. The active floor may be provided in an belt in which the driven side has a lower friction material so as to improve belt life.

column13: Die Erfindung bezieht sich auf einen Mähdrescher (10) mit einem Schrägförderer (18), der eingerichtet ist, Erntegut in den Mähdrescher (10) zu fördern, mit im Eingriff mit dem Erdboden befindlichen Mitteln, die eingerichtet sind, den Mähdrescher (10) mit einer Erntegeschwindigkeit über den Erdboden zu bewegen und mit einer Steuerung (80), die eingerichtet ist, die Erntegeschwindigkeit in Abhängigkeit vom Signal eines Schrägfördererkraftsensors (76) einzustellen. Es wird vorgeschlagen, dass der Schrägfördererkraftsensor (76) einen ersten Fühler umfasst, der eingerichtet ist, die Position einer Trommel (66) zu erfassen, die an der Oberseite des Ernteguts aufliegt und durch das Erntegut vertikal bewegbar ist, dass der Bewegungsbereich der Trommel (66) durch einen Anschlag begrenzt ist, und dass ein zweiter Fühler des Schrägfördererkraftsensors (76) eingerichtet ist, die von der Trommel (66) auf den Anschlag ausgeübte Kraft zu erfassen, wenn die Trommel (66) bei relativ hohen Gutdurchsätzen am Anschlag anliegt.

column12: Method Of Automatically Changing Wheel Toe Angle
column13: A method for changing the track of a vehicle ( 100 ) having first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ) disposed on opposing sides of the vehicle ( 100 ) along a line generally perpendicular to the direction of travel of the vehicle, the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 are supported on first and second wheel supports ( 114, 116, 204 ) to permit the track of the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ) to be adjusted, at least one actuator ( 218, 220 ) is coupled to at least one wheel of the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ) and is configured to change the toe angle of said first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ), and an electronic control unit ( 402 ) is coupled to the actuator ( 218, 220 ) that is configured to command the actuator ( 218, 220 ) to change the toe angle, the method comprising the steps of changing the toe angle of the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ); rolling the vehicle ( 100 ) on the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ) over the ground to generate opposing lateral forces on the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ); and applying the opposing lateral forces to the first and second wheel supports ( 114, 116, 204 ) to change the track of the first and second wheels ( 108, 110 ).

column12: Agricultural harvester with propulsion load shifting between dual engines
column13: An agricultural harvester includes a first power unit which is couplable with a first primary load. The first primary load includes a threshing system load. A second power unit has a threshold power output and is couplable with a second primary load. The second primary load includes a propulsion load. A first motor/generator is mechanically coupled with the first power unit. A second motor/generator is mechanically coupled with the second power unit. The second motor/generator and the first motor/generator are electrically coupled together. At least one electrical processing circuit is coupled with each of the first motor/generator and the second motor/generator. The at least one electrical processing circuit is configured for selectively transferring electrical power from the first motor/generator to the second motor/generator, when the second power unit is at or above the threshold power output.

By means of the dispensing device, the flexible pouch can be properly sealed without a loss of functionality due to contamination. Furthermore, the dispensing device aids in dispensing of the tissue by frictionally engaging the tissues. <IMAGE>

column12: Sich hin- und herbewegende Messeranordnung für ein landwirtschaftliches Gerät
column13: Messeranordnung eines landwirtschaftlichen Geräts (100), das als Schneidwerk mit seitlich fördernden Bandförderern ausgeführt ist und einen sich in seitlicher Richtung über die gesamte Breite des Geräts (100) erstreckenden Hauptrahmen (102) umfasst, an dem ein Förderersystem (104) abgestützt ist, welches Förderersystem (104) einen mittigen Förderer (110) mit einer endlosen Gurtanordnung mit einem Fördergurt (138), sowie einen linken Förderer (106) und einen rechten Förderer (108) umfasst, welche ausgelegt und angeordnet sind, vom Boden abgeschnittene Pflanzen einer Öffnung (112) im mittleren, rückwärtigen Abschnitt des Rahmens (102) zuzuführen, wobei der linke Förderer (106) und der rechte Förderer (108) an gegenüber liegenden Seiten des mittigen Förderers (110) angeordnet sind und jeweils erste und zweite endlose Gurtanordnungen mit Fördergurten (120, 132) umfassen, die jeweils als erste und zweite Schleife geformt sind, die jeweils innere Enden umfassen, die dem mittigen Förderer (110) benachbart sind, wobei die endlosen Fördergurte (120, 132) des linken Förderers (106) und des rechten Förderers (108) jeweils angeordnet sind, Erntegut seitlich auf den mittigen Förderer (110) zu fördern, wobei die Messeranordnung folgendes umfasst:einen sich hin- und herbewegenden Messerbalken (144), der sich im Wesentlichen über die gesamte Breite des Geräts (100) erstreckt, entlang der vorlaufenden Kante des Geräts (100) angeordnet ist, um das stehende Erntegut im Wesentlichen über die ganze Breite des Geräts (100) abzuschneiden, und eine Vielzahl an stationären Führungen (146) umfasst, die voneinander beabstandet an einem stationären Messerträger (148) angebracht sind, welcher sich im Wesentlichen über die gesamte Breite des Geräts (100) erstreckt, wobei der Hauptrahmen (102) die rückwärtigen Enden einer Vielzahl beabstandeter, sich nach vorn erstreckender Arme schwenkbar abstützt, die wiederum die am Gerät (100) befestigten Förderer (106, 108, 110) und den sich hin- und herbewegenden Messerzusammenbau mit dem Messerträger (148) und dem Messerbalken (144) an ihren vorderen Enden abstützen,ein erstes, langgestrecktes Gleitelement (150) mit daran befestigen Klingen (154), das an einer vorlaufenden Kante des Geräts (100) an dessen linker Seite angeordnet ist,ein zweites, langgestrecktes Gleitelement (152) mit daran befestigen Klingen (154), das an einer vorlaufenden Kante des Geräts (100) an dessen rechter Seite angeordnet ist,wobei die Gleitelemente (150, 152) benachbarte Enden umfassen und sich zwecks gleichzeitiger Hin- und Herbewegung in gegenüberliegende Richtungen kollinear erstrecken und in seitlicher, sich quer zur Vorwärtsrichtung des Geräts (100) bei einem Erntevorgang erstreckender Richtung verschiebbar am Messerträger (148) gelagert sind, undeinen sich hin- und herbewegenden Messerantriebszusammenbau (156),dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass der Messerantriebszusammenbau (156) einen mit dem ersten Gleitelement (150) antriebsverbundenen ersten Winkelhebel (168), um das erste Gleitelement (150) in seitlicher Richtung hin- und herzubewegen, und einen mit dem zweiten Gleitelement (152) antriebsverbundenen zweiten Winkelhebel (170) umfasst, um das zweite Gleitelement (152) in seitlicher Richtung hin- und herzubewegen, wobei die Winkelhebel (168, 170) jeweils innerhalb einer Schleife des endlosen Gurts (120, 132) des in seitlicher Richtung des Schneidwerks fördernden, linken Förderers (106) oder des in seitlicher Richtung des Schneidwerks fördernden, rechten Förderers (108) angeordnet sind;dass die Winkelhebel (168, 170) an wenigstens einem sich unterhalb der ersten oder zweiten Schleife erstreckenden Fördererträgerarm (208) abgestützt sind, der an seinem rückwärtigen Ende am Hauptrahmen (102) schwenkbar abgestützt ist, sodass der Fördererträgerarm (208) um eine horizontale und sich seitlich erstreckende Achse (212) schwenken kann, und an seinem vorderen Ende an einem Gleitschuh (216) befestigt ist, der wiederum mit dem stationären Messerträger (148) gekoppelt ist, sodass der Fördererträgerarm (208) gemeinsam mit dem Messerantriebszusammenbau (156) um eine sich horizontal und seitlich erstreckende Achse schwenken kann;dass ein sich von vorn nach hinten erstreckender Messerantriebsrahmen (180), dessen vorderer Teil sich innerhalb einer Schleife des endlosen Gurts (120, 132) des in seitlicher Richtung des Schneidwerks fördernden, linken Förderers (106) oder des in seitlicher Richtung des Schneidwerks fördernden, rechten Förderers (108) erstreckt, ein am stationären Messerträger (148) befestigtes, vorderes Ende und ein am Fördererträgerarm (208) befestigtes, rückwärtiges Ende aufweist,und dass die Winkelhebel (168, 170) jeweils um erste und zweite, quer zur Oberfläche des endlosen Gurtes angeordnete Achsen schwenkbar am Messerantriebsrahmen (180) gelagert sind.

column12: HARVESTER LOAD CONTROL SYSTEM
column13: A method of controlling a multiengine harvester includes the steps of operating the harvester in a first mode, operating the harvester in a second mode, and selecting less than all of the power absorbing loads to be driven. In the first mode, the harvester is operated using a first engine and a second engine to drive the plurality of power absorbing loads. In the second mode, the harvester is operated with the second engine being uncoupled from all of the power absorbing loads. In the selecting step, less than all of the power absorbing loads are selected to be driven dependent upon the sensed load on the first engine while operating in the second mode. The first engine is incapable of driving all of the power absorbing loads.

column12: THROUGHPUT CONTROL FOR COMBINES
column13: An agricultural combine having a supporting structure that is driven by grou nd engaging wheels at a harvesting speed by a propulsion assembly. The combine is also provided with crop processing assemblies for processing a harvested crop. A feederhouse directs the harvested crop material to the crop processing assemblies. A feederhouse force sensor senses the force exerted by the harvested crap material as it passes through the feederhouse. The feederhouse force signal is directly related to crop throughput. An operator control in the operator's cab of the combine provides a loss rate signal that is also directed to the electronic controller. The electronic controller converts th e loss rate signal into a desired feederhouse force signal. The electronic controller regulates the forward speed (harvesting speed) of the combine so that the desired feederhouse forc e signal is equal to the actual feederhouse force signal. The harvesting speed regulatio n can be modified or overridden by moisture signals from a moisture sensor located in the feederhouse for sensing the moisture content of harvested crop.

column12: Agricultural harvester with electric power transfer between dual power units
column13: An agricultural harvester (10) includes a first power unit which is couplable with a first primary load (18). The first primary load (18) includes a threshing system load. A second power unit has a threshold power output and is couplable with a second primary load (26). The second primary load includes a propulsion load. A first motor/generator (22) is mechanically coupled with the first power unit. A second motor/generator (30) is mechanically coupled with the second power unit. The second motor/generator (30) and the first motor/generator (22) are electrically coupled together. At least one electrical processing circuit (50) is coupled with each of the first motor/generator (22) and the second motor/generator (30). The at least one electrical processing circuit (50) is configured for selectively transferring electrical power from the first motor/generator (22) to the second motor/generator (30), when the second power unit is at or above the threshold power output.

column12: INSTALACION DE CONTROL DE RENDIMIENTO PARA COSECHADORAS COMBINADAS Y EL METODO PARA CONTROLAR LA VELOCIDAD DE COSECHA QUE LLEVA A LA PRACTICA DICHA INSTALACION
column13: Sistema de control de rendimiento para una máquina agrícola combinada donde la fuerza ascendente sobre el tambor delantero del alimentador es medida y usada para controlar la velocidad de cosechado de la máquina combinada. Máquina combinada agrícola que tiene una estructura de soporte que es impulsada por ruedas que se vinculan con el suelo a una velocidad de cosecha por un conjunto propulsor. La máquina combinada también está provista con conjuntos procesadores de cultivo para procesar un cultivo cosechado. Un sensor de fuerza del alimentador detecta la fuerza ejercida por el material de cultivo cosechado a medida que pasa a través del alimentador. La senal de fuerza del alimentador está directamente relacionada con el rendimiento de cultivo. Un control de operador en la cabina del conductor de la máquina provee una senal de régimen de pérdida que también es dirigida al controlador electrónico. El controlador eléctrico convierta la senal de régimen de pérdida en una senal de fuerza deseada del alimentador. El controlador electrónico regula la velocidad hacia adelante (velocidad de cosecha) de la máquina combinada de modo que la senal de fuerza del alimentador deseada es igual a la senal de fuerza del alimentador real. La regulación de la velocidad de cosecha puede ser modificada o contrarrestada por senales de humedad provenientes de un sensor de humedad ubicado en el alojamiento alimentador para detectar el contenido de humedad del cultivo cosechado.

column12: Harvester load control system
column13: A method of controlling a multiengine harvester including the steps of operating the harvester in a first mode, operating the harvester in a second mode, and selecting less than all of the power absorbing loads to be driven. In the first mode, the harvester is operated using a first engine and a second engine to drive the plurality of power absorbing loads. In the second mode, the harvester is operated with the second engine being uncoupled from all of the power absorbing loads. In the selecting step, less than all of the power absorbing loads are selected to be driven dependent upon the sensed load on the first engine while operating in the second mode. The first engine is incapable of driving all of the power absorbing loads.

The electronic combine controller regulates the harvesting speed of the combine in response to the moisture signal.

column12: Throughput control for combines using feederhouse signal
column13: An agricultural combine having a supporting structure that is driven by ground engaging wheels at a harvesting speed by a propulsion assembly. The combine is also provided with crop processing assemblies for processing a harvested crop. A feederhouse directs the harvested crop material to the crop processing assemblies. A feederhouse force sensor senses the force exerted by the harvested crop material as it passes through the feederhouse. The feederhouse force signal is directly related to crop throughput. An operator control in the operator's cab of the combine provides a loss rate signal that is also directed to the electronic controller. The electronic controller converts the loss rate signal into a desired feederhouse force signal. The electronic controller regulates the forward speed or harvesting speed of the combine so that the desired feederhouse force signal is equal to the actual feederhouse force signal. The harvesting speed regulation can be modified or overridden by moisture signals from a moisture sensor located in the feederhouse for sensing the moisture content of harvested crop.
column15: COERS BRUCE ALAN;;BURKE DANIEL JAMES;;COOPER WILLIAM F;;LITTKE JERRY DEAN;;MERTINS KARL-HEINZ

column12: Harvester feedrate control with tilt compensation
column13: A combine with a throughput dependent speed control includes an angle sensor responsive to uphill, downhill and sidehill slopes. When the combine is angled from a level position, harvest speed is lowered to prevent grain losses from increasing above a target level. The control continuously learns tilt angle, loss and throughput correlation, and the speed reduction is selected based upon the learned correlation. In the preferred embodiment, throughput is estimated utilizing rotor variable drive actuator pressure (RVDAP), and a target RVDAP is modified for short periods of time in accordance with the learned correlation.
column15: COERS BRUCE ALAN;;BURKE DANIEL JAMES;;COOPER WILLIAM F;;LITTKE JERRY DEAN;;MERTINS KARL-HEINZ O

column12: Combinada agrìcola para colher, debulhar e separar uma safra agrìcola
column13: "COMBINADA AGRìCOLA PARA COLHER, DEBULHAR E SEPARAR UMA SAFRA AGRICOLA". Uma combinada agrícola possuindo uma estrutura de suporte que é acionada pelas rodas de engate com o chão a uma velocidade de colheita por um conjunto de propulsão. A combinada também é fornecida com um conjunto de debulhar que é suprido com material de safra colhido por um depósito de grãos. O depósito de grãos é fornecido com um sensor de umidade para perceber a umidade do material de safra colhido à medida que o mesmo passa através do depósito de grãos. O sensor de umidade produz um sinal de umidade que é direcionado para um controlador de combinada eletrónico. O controlador de combinada eletrónico regula a velocidade de colheita da combinada em resposta ao sinal de umidade.

column12: Rowing Exercise Machines Having A Configurable Rowing Feel
column13: Among other things, a rowing exercise machine includes a movable inertial element, an eddy current brake coupled to the movable inertial element, a rowing grip coupled to the movable inertial element, and control circuitry coupled to the eddy current brake to cause a resistance to motion of the rowing grip during part of a rowing stroke. The resistance to motion of the rowing grip during the drive phase of the rowing stroke conforms to a target feel for a rower. The target feel corresponds to a feel for a rower of a target other rowing exercise machine or other target feel of interest.

column12: Crop moisture sensor for controlling harvesting speed
column13: An agricultural combine having a supporting structure that is driven by ground engaging wheels at a harvesting speed by a propulsion assembly. The combine is also provided with a threshing assembly that is supplied harvested crop material by a feederhouse. The feederhouse is provided with a moisture sensor for sensing the moisture of harvested crop material as it passes through the feederhouse. The moisture sensor produces a moisture signal that is directed to an electronic combine controller. The electronic combine controller regulates the harvesting speed of the combine in response to the moisture signal.

column12: Surgical/medical irrigator with removable tip and integrated suction conduit
column13: An irrigator (20) useful for surgical and medical procedures. The irrigator includes a handpiece (22) to which a tip assembly (30) is attached. The handpiece (22) includes a drain tube (50) that extends through the body of the handpiece and outside of the handpiece to the complementary suction system. The tip assembly includes a discharge tube (32) that is snap secured into the front of the handpiece and a suction tube (48) that seats in the open front end of the drain tube. A removable splash shield (181) is attached to the front end of the tip assembly. A trigger (44) allows one-handed control of, the position of the handpiece, the on/off state of the irrigator and the rate at which fluid is discharged from the irrigator. A rechargeable power pack (222) can be used to supply the energization current needed to activate a number of different handpieces at different speeds.

column12: UN CONTROL DE VELOCIDAD Y METODO PARA CONTROLAR LA OPERACION DE UNA COSECHADORA CON COMPENSACION DE INCLINACION Y LA INSTALACION DE CONTROL DE COSECHA QUE SE CONSTITUYE
column13: Control de régimen de carga que responde a la inclinación de una cosechadora. Una cosechadora combinada con un control de velocidad que depende del rendimiento, incluye un sensor de ángulo que responde a las pendientes cuesta arriba, cuesta abajo y de ladera. Cuando la cosechadora combinada está en ángulo desde una posición nivelada, la velocidad de cosecha es descendida para impedir que aumenten las pérdidas de grano por encima de un nivel objetivo. El control registra continuamente la correlación entre el ángulo de inclinación, la pérdida y el rendimiento, y la reducción de velocidad se selecciona en base a la correlación registrada. En la realización preferida, el rendimiento es estimado utilizando la presión de accionador del accionamiento variable del rotor (RVDAP), y una presión objetivo del accionador del accionamiento variable del rotor es modificada por períodos de tiempo cortos de acuerdo con la correlación registrada.

column12: Rowing exercise machines having a configurable rowing feel
column13: Among other things, a rowing exercise machine includes a movable inertial element, an eddy current brake coupled to the movable inertial element, a rowing grip coupled to the movable inertial element, and control circuitry coupled to the eddy current brake to cause a resistance to motion of the rowing grip during part of a rowing stroke. column12: Package for tissues comprising a flexible pouch and a re-usable dispensing device
column13:
The invention relates to Package (1) comprising:
 a flexible pouch (3) containing a stack of tissues (5), the pouch comprising a top surface (7), a bottom surface (9), a side surface (11, 12, 14), a pre-formed first dispensing aperture (13) in the top surface and a cover member (15) covering the first dispensing aperture, and a relatively rigid re-usable dispensing device (17) comprising attachment means (18, 33, 35, 37, 40, 41, 43, 45, 47, 55, 56, 59, 60)for releasable attachment to the pouch, 
characterised in that 
the cover member (15) is completely removable from the first dispensing aperture (13), 
the top surface (7) of the pouch comprising a sealing area (21) , which sealing area forms a substantially closed contour around the first dispensing aperture (13), 
the dispensing device (17) comprising a base member (23, 39, 47, 56, 58) having a second dispensing aperture (25, 46, 49, 50), a connecting area (27, 47, 56, 58) for sealingly engaging the sealing area (21) of the pouch, and a closure member (29, 32, 36, 38, 51, 55, 60) for sealingly closing the second dispensing aperture (25, 46, 49, 50) by contacting the base member (23, 47, 56, 58). By means of the dispensing device, the flexible pouch can be properly sealed without a loss of functionality due to contamination. Furthermore, the dispensing device aids in dispensing of the tissue by frictionally engaging the tissues.

column12: Combinada agrìcola para colher, debulhar e separar uma safra agrìcola, e, processo para controle da velocidade de colheita de uma combinada agrìcola
column13: "COMBINADA AGRìCOLA PARA COLHER, DEBULHAR E SEPARAR UMA SAFRA AGRìCOLA, E, PROCESSO PARA CONTROLE DA VELOCIDADE DE COLHEITA DE UMA COMBINADA AGRìCOLA". Uma combinada agrícola possuindo uma estrutura de suporte que é acionada por rodas de engate com o chão a uma velocidade de colheita por um conjunto de impulsão. A combinada também é fornecida com conjuntos de processamento de safra para processar uma safra colhida. Um depósito de grãos direciona o material de safra colhido para os conjuntos de processamento de safra. Um sensor de força de depósito de grãos percebe a força exercida pelo material de safra colhido à medida que o mesmo passa através do depósito de grãos. O sinal de força do depósito de grãos é relacionado diretamente com a produtividade de safra. Um controle de operador na cabine do operador da combinada fornece um sinal de taxa de perda que também é direcionado para o controlador eletrónico. O controlador eletrónico converte o sinal de taxa de perda em um sinal de força de depósito de grãos desejado. O controlador eletrónico regula a velocidade de avanço (velocidade de colheita) da combinada de forma que o sinal de força do depósito de grãos desejado seja igual ao sinal de força do depósito de grãos real. A regulagem da velocidade de colheita pode ser modificada ou eliminada por sinais de umidade de um sensor de umidade localizado no depósito de grãos para perceber o teor de umidade da safra colhida.

column12: Controle de velocidade em uma colheitadeira, método para controlar a operação de uma colheitadeira, e, sistema de controle de colheita de uma combinada
column13: "CONTROLE DE VELOCIDADE EM UMA COLHEITADEIRA, MéTODO PARA CONTROLAR A OPERAçãO DE UMA COLHEITADEIRA E, SISTEMA DE CONTROLE DE COLHEITA DE UMA COMBINADA". Uma combinada com um controle de velocidade que depende da produção inclui um sensor de ângulo que responde a inclinação morro acima, morro abaixo e ao longo do morro. Quando a combinada é angulada em relação a uma posição nivelada, a velocidade de colheita é diminuída para prevenir que as perdas de grão aumentem acima de um nível visado. O controle aprende continuamente a correlação entre o ângulo de inclinação, perda e produção, e a redução de velocidade é selecionada com base na correlação aprendida. Na modalidade preferida, a produção é estimada por meio da pressão do atuador de acionamento variável do rotor (RVDAP), e uma RVDAP visada é modificada por curtos períodos de tempo, de acordo com a correlação aprendida.

column12: Kathodenkopf mit Fadenschutzmerkmalen
column13: Eine Kathodenbaugruppe, die bestimmte Merkmale enthält, die ausgelegt sind, um die Integrität eines darin enthaltenen Fadens zu schützen, wird offenbart. Insbesondere ist die Kathodenbaugruppe konfiguriert, Beschädigung an dem Faden zu verhindern, sollte er einen anderen Abschnitt der Kathodenbaugruppe versehentlich kontaktieren. Bei einem Ausführungsbeispiel wird eine Merkmale der vorliegenden Erfindung enthaltende Röntgenröhre offenbart. Die Röntgenröhre enthält eine evakuierte Hülle, die eine Kathodenbaugruppe und eine Anode enthält. Die Kathodenbaugruppe enthält einen Kopfabschnitt mit einer Kopfoberfläche. Ein Schlitz ist auf der Kopfoberfläche definiert, und ein elektronen-emittierender Faden ist in dem Schlitz enthalten. Eine Schutzoberfläche ist auf der Kopfoberfläche in der Nähe eines Zentralabschnitts des Fadens definiert. Die Schutzoberfläche besteht bei einer Ausführungsform aus Wolfram und ist konfiguriert, das Verschmelzen des Fadens mit der Schutzoberfläche zu verhindern, sollte der Faden die Schutzoberfläche versehentlich kontaktieren.

column12: CATHODE HEAD WITH FILAMENT PROTECTION STRUCTURE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a cathode assembly including a structure designed to protect perfectness of a housed filament.

SOLUTION: The cathode assembly is structured so that a damage of a filament can be prevented in case of the filament contacting incidentally with a different part of the cathode assembly. As an example of applications, this structure of the cathode assembly is provided in an X-ray tube. The X-ray tube contains a vacuum case in which the cathode assembly and an anode are housed. The cathode assembly contains a head part with a head surface. A groove hole is formed on the head surface and the groove hole contains an electron discharging filament. A protective surface is formed on the head surface closest to the center part of the filament. In an application example, the protective surface is made of tungsten and is structured so that in case of the filament contacting incidentally with the protective surface, a fusion of the filament with the protective surface is prevented.

column12: RUBBER COMPOSITION CONTAINING STYRENE/BUTADIENE ELASTOMER AND SILICA REINFORCEMENT AND TIRE
column13:
A rubber composition is disclosed containing, based on parts by weight per 100 parts by weight of the rubber (phr), 
(A) conjugated diene-based elastomers comprising: 
(1) from 40 to 90 phr, alternately 60 to 80 phr, of a styrene/butadiene elastomer having a molecular weight profile comprising a weight average molecular weight (Mw) in a range of from 500,000 to 800,000, with the low molecular weight content having a weight average molecular weight (Mw) of up to 150,000 being limited to a maximum of seven weight percent of the styrene/butadiene elastomer, and 
(2) from 60 to 10 phr of at least one additional conjugated diene-based elastomer; 
 
(B) from 40 to 150 phr of a filler comprising a combination of carbon black and silica together with a coupling agent having a moiety reactive or interactive with hydroxyl groups on the silica and another different moiety reactive or interactive with the diene-based elastomers. Also, a tire comprising this rubber composition is disclosed.

column12: Method of manufacturing phosphosilicate optical fibre preforms and optical fibers drawn therefrom
column13: A method of manufacturing a cane suitable for forming an optical fiber, and a method of forming an optical fiber from the cane. A core composition having about 20% to 30% by weight of P 2 O 5  is formed. An inner cladding composition is formed on an outer surface of the core composition and the core composition and the inner cladding composition are consolidated into a preform having a core and an inner cladding while substantially closing a center line hole of the preform. An outer cladding composition is formed on the preform to define a cane. The cane can then be transformed into an optical fiber.

column12: Cathode head having filament protection features
column13: A cathode assembly including certain features designed to protect the integrity of a filament contained therein is disclosed. In particular, the cathode assembly is configured to prevent damage to the filament should it inadvertently contact another portion of the cathode assembly. In an example embodiment, an x-ray tube incorporating features of the present invention is disclosed. The x-ray tube includes an evacuated enclosure containing a cathode assembly and an anode. The cathode assembly includes a head portion having a head surface. A slot is defined on the head surface and an electron-emitting filament is included in the slot. A protective surface is defined on the head surface proximate to a central portion of the filament. The protective surface in one embodiment is composed of tungsten and is configure to prevent fusing of the filament to the protective surface should the filament inadvertently contact the protective surface.

column12: Cathode head having filament protection features
column13: A cathode assembly including certain features designed to protect the integrity of a filament contained therein is disclosed. In particular, the cathode assembly is configured to prevent damage to the filament should it inadvertently contact another portion of the cathode assembly. In an example embodiment, an x-ray tube incorporating features of the present invention is disclosed. The x-ray tube includes an evacuated enclosure containing a cathode assembly and an anode. The cathode assembly includes a head portion having a head surface. A slot is defined on the head surface and an electron-emitting filament is included in the slot. A protective surface is defined on the head surface proximate to a central portion of the filament. The protective surface in one embodiment is composed of tungsten and is configure to prevent fusing of the filament to the protective surface should the filament inadvertently contact the protective surface.

column12: CONTROL DE RENDIMIENTO PARA COSECHADORAS COMBINADAS.
column13: Cosechadora combinada agrícola que tiene una estructura de soporte que es impulsada por ruedas que se vinculan con el suelo a una velocidad de cosecha por un conjunto propulsor. La cosechadora combinada también está provista con un conjunto trillador que es impulsado por un accionamiento detector de torque variable. El accionamiento detector de torque variable es manejado por fluido hidráulico presurizado. Un sensor hidráulico en comunicacion hidráulica con el accionamiento detector de torque variable provee una senal de presion hidráulica real que es dirigida a un controlador electronico. Un control de operador en la cabina del conductor de la máquina provee una senal de régimen de pérdida que también es dirigida al controlador electronico. El controlador electronico convierte la senal de régimen de pérdida en una senal de presion hidráulica deseada. El controlador electronico regula la velocidad hacia adelante (velocidad de cosecha) de la máquina combinada de modo que la senal de presion hidráulica deseada es igual a la presion de senal real. La regulacion de la velocidad de cosecha puede ser modificada o contrarrestada por senales de humedad provenientes de un sensor de humedad ubicado en el alojamiento alimentador para detectar el contenido de humedad del cultivo cosechado.
